422
00:30:47.387 --> 00:30:48.929
{\pos(97.275)}Home sweet home.

423
00:30:51.433 --> 00:30:54.310
{\pos(97.275)}So. this is. like.
your house?

424
00:30:55.103 --> 00:30:56.395
{\pos(97.275)}Wait a sec...

425
00:30:56.480 --> 00:30:59.231
{\pos(97.275)}You're the guy
who pretended he was
a recorded message!

426
00:30:59.316 --> 00:31:01.317
{\pos(97.275)}No. that was
someone else.

427
00:31:14.873 --> 00:31:16.165
{\pos(97.275)}Can I hold your hand?

428
00:31:16.958 --> 00:31:17.958
{\pos(97.275)}Uh. no.

429
00:31:28.261 --> 00:31:30.429
{\pos(97.275)}When we got adopted
by a bald guy.

430
00:31:30.514 --> 00:31:33.140
{\pos(97.275)}I thought this'd be
more like Annie.

431
00:31:33.809 --> 00:31:35.810
{\pos(97.275)}(GROWLING)

432
00:31:42.067 --> 00:31:43.359
{\pos(97.275)}No. hey!

433
00:31:47.447 --> 00:31:50.616
{\pos(97.275)}Kyle. these are not treats.
These are guests.

434
00:31:50.700 --> 00:31:53.327
{\pos(97.275)}Girls.
this is Kyle. my

435
00:31:53.412 --> 00:31:54.453
{\pos(97.275)}dog.

436
00:31:55.288 --> 00:31:56.539
{\pos(97.275)}(SNARLS)

437
00:31:57.040 --> 00:31:58.374
{\pos(97.275)}Ooh! Fluffy doggy!

438
00:32:01.002 --> 00:32:02.294
{\pos(97.275)}(YELPING)

439
00:32:03.839 --> 00:32:04.964
{\pos(97.275)}What kind of dog
is that?

440
00:32:05.048 --> 00:32:07.675
{\pos(97.275)}He is a...
I don't know.

441
00:32:08.552 --> 00:32:11.762
{\pos(97.275)}MARGO: Do you really think
that this is an appropriate
place for little kids?

442
00:32:12.264 --> 00:32:13.931
{\pos(97.275)}'Cause it's not.

443
00:32:15.016 --> 00:32:17.351
{\pos(97.275)}No! No!
Stay away from there!

444
00:32:17.436 --> 00:32:19.019
{\pos(97.275)}It's fragile.

445
00:32:20.480 --> 00:32:21.480
{\pos(97.275)}(GASPS)

446
00:32:21.565 --> 00:32:25.025
{\pos(97.275)}Well. I suppose
the plan will
work with two.

447
00:32:25.110 --> 00:32:27.903
{\pos(97.275)}EDITH: Hey!
It's dark in here.

448
00:32:30.782 --> 00:32:33.159
{\pos(97.275)}It poked a hole
in my juice box.

449
00:32:38.123 --> 00:32:39.373
{\pos(97.275)}As you can see.

450
00:32:39.458 --> 00:32:42.960
{\pos(97.275)}I have provided everything
a child might need.

451
00:32:44.838 --> 00:32:45.838
{\pos(97.275)}All right.

452
00:32:46.173 --> 00:32:49.425
{\pos(97.275)}Uh... Okay.
As I was saying... Hey!
(CRASHING)

453
00:32:50.635 --> 00:32:51.677
{\pos(97.275)}Somebody broke that.

454
00:32:52.137 --> 00:32:55.806
{\pos(97.275)}Okay. okay.
Clearly. we need
to set some rules.

455
00:32:55.891 --> 00:32:57.725
{\pos(97.275)}Rule number one.

456
00:32:57.809 --> 00:33:00.352
{\pos(97.275)}You will not
touch anything.

457
00:33:00.437 --> 00:33:02.313
{\pos(97.275)}Uh-huh.
What about the floor?

458
00:33:02.731 --> 00:33:04.773
{\pos(97.275)}Yes. you may
touch the floor.

459
00:33:04.858 --> 00:33:06.233
{\pos(97.275)}What about the air?

460
00:33:06.318 --> 00:33:08.402
{\pos(97.275)}Yes. you may
touch the air!

461
00:33:08.487 --> 00:33:09.528
{\pos(97.275)}What about this?

462
00:33:10.906 --> 00:33:12.239
{\pos(97.275)}(EXCLAIMS)

463
00:33:12.699 --> 00:33:14.658
{\pos(97.275)}Where did you get that?
Found it.

464
00:33:14.743 --> 00:33:18.496
{\pos(97.275)}Okay. Rule number two.
You will not bother me
while I'm working.

465
00:33:18.580 --> 00:33:20.498
{\pos(97.275)}Rule number three.

466
00:33:20.582 --> 00:33:25.044
{\pos(97.275)}You will not cry or whine
or laugh or giggle

467
00:33:25.378 --> 00:33:27.755
{\pos(97.275)}or sneeze
or burp or fart!

468
00:33:28.423 --> 00:33:32.760
{\pos(97.275)}So. no. no. no
annoying sounds.
All right?

469
00:33:32.844 --> 00:33:34.678
{\pos(97.275)}Does this count
as annoying?

470
00:33:34.763 --> 00:33:36.430
{\pos(97.275)}(POPPING)

471
00:33:38.433 --> 00:33:39.600
{\pos(97.275)}Very!

472
00:33:40.101 --> 00:33:41.310
{\pos(97.275)}(SIGHS)

473
00:33:42.103 --> 00:33:44.688
{\pos(97.275)}I will see you
in six hours.

474
00:33:46.775 --> 00:33:50.694
{\pos(97.275)}Okay. don't worry.
Everything's going
to be fine.

475
00:33:51.321 --> 00:33:55.699
{\pos(97.275)}We're gonna be
really happy here.
Right? Agnes?

476
00:33:57.118 --> 00:33:58.327
{\pos(97.275)}Mmm?

477
00:34:00.956 --> 00:34:01.956
{\pos(97.275)}(EXCLAIMS)

478
00:34:02.457 --> 00:34:04.291
{\pos(97.275)}(SPEAKING GIBBERISH)

479
00:34:05.669 --> 00:34:07.378
{\pos(97.275)}(CLICKING)

480
00:34:09.506 --> 00:34:11.549
{\pos(97.275)}(UPBEAT POP MUSIC PLAYING)

481
00:34:23.478 --> 00:34:27.273
{\pos(97.275)}Uh. question.
What are these?

482
00:34:28.191 --> 00:34:32.653
{\pos(97.275)}A dozen boogie robots!
Boogie! (LAUGHING)

483
00:34:32.737 --> 00:34:34.738
{\pos(97.275)}Look at this. Watch me!

484
00:34:34.823 --> 00:34:36.323
{\pos(97.275)}(MUSIC STOPS)

485
00:34:38.660 --> 00:34:41.328
{\pos(97.275)}Cookie robots.
I said cookie robots.

486
00:34:41.913 --> 00:34:44.498
{\pos(97.275)}Why are you so old?

487
00:34:46.960 --> 00:34:48.586
{\pos(97.275)}Okay. I'm on it.

488
00:34:49.504 --> 00:34:50.838
{\pos(97.275)}Hello?

489
00:35:06.521 --> 00:35:07.771
{\pos(97.275)}TV!

490
00:35:09.274 --> 00:35:11.150
{\pos(97.275)}(KYLE GROWLING)

491
00:35:25.832 --> 00:35:27.166
{\pos(97.275)}(WHIMPERS)

492
00:35:27.626 --> 00:35:28.626
{\pos(97.275)}MARGO: What is that?

493
00:35:28.710 --> 00:35:29.918
{\pos(97.275)}Wow!
Look at that!

494
00:35:30.003 --> 00:35:31.462
{\pos(97.275)}That is cool!

495
00:35:32.297 --> 00:35:33.589
{\pos(97.275)}Come on!

496
00:35:34.090 --> 00:35:36.383
{\pos(97.275)}I don't think
he's a dentist.

497
00:35:43.767 --> 00:35:45.059
{\pos(97.275)}(WHIMPERS)

498
00:35:50.231 --> 00:35:52.024
{\pos(97.275)}We've been working
on this for a while.

499
00:35:52.108 --> 00:35:54.902
{\pos(97.275)}It's a anti-gravity serum.

500
00:35:56.154 --> 00:35:57.571
{\pos(97.275)}(EXCLAIMING)

501
00:35:58.031 --> 00:35:59.365
{\pos(97.275)}(SCREAMING)

502
00:36:00.617 --> 00:36:03.994
{\pos(97.275)}I meant to close that.
He'll be all right.
I'm sure.

503
00:36:04.079 --> 00:36:05.621
{\pos(97.275)}Do the effects wear off?

504
00:36:05.705 --> 00:36:07.164
{\pos(97.275)}Uh. so far.

505
00:36:07.248 --> 00:36:09.249
{\pos(97.275)}no. No. they don't.

506
00:36:10.794 --> 00:36:13.879
{\pos(97.275)}And here. of course.
is the new weapon
you ordered.

507
00:36:14.005 --> 00:36:15.464
{\pos(97.275)}(FARTING)

508
00:36:17.550 --> 00:36:18.509
{\pos(97.275)}No. no.

509
00:36:18.593 --> 00:36:22.471
{\pos(97.275)}I said "dart gun."
not... Okay.

510
00:36:23.098 --> 00:36:25.849
{\pos(97.275)}Oh. yes.
'Cause I was wondering

511
00:36:25.934 --> 00:36:28.519
{\pos(97.275)}under what circumstances
would we use this?

512
00:36:28.603 --> 00:36:30.062
{\pos(97.275)}But. anyway.

513
00:36:30.146 --> 00:36:33.607
{\pos(97.275)}What I really wanted
to show you was this.

514
00:36:38.363 --> 00:36:41.490
{\pos(97.275)}Now those are
cookie robots!

515
00:36:42.617 --> 00:36:45.869
{\pos(97.275)}AGNES: (SINGING)
La. la. la. la
I love unicorns

516
00:36:45.954 --> 00:36:49.623
{\pos(97.275)}What are you doing here?
I told you to stay
in the kitchen!

517
00:36:49.708 --> 00:36:52.292
{\pos(97.275)}We got bored.
What is this place?

518
00:36:52.544 --> 00:36:54.211
{\pos(97.275)}Can I drink this?

519
00:36:54.295 --> 00:36:56.755
{\pos(97.275)}Do you want to explode?

520
00:36:57.215 --> 00:36:58.298
{\pos(97.275)}(EXCLAIMS)

521
00:36:58.383 --> 00:36:59.383
{\pos(97.275)}Gru!

522
00:36:59.467 --> 00:37:01.468
{\pos(97.275)}Get back
in the kitchen!

523
00:37:01.553 --> 00:37:03.679
{\pos(97.275)}Will you play with us?
No.

524
00:37:04.097 --> 00:37:06.306
{\pos(97.275)}Why?
Because I'm busy.

525
00:37:06.391 --> 00:37:07.933
{\pos(97.275)}(SCOFFS)
Doing what?

526
00:37:08.017 --> 00:37:09.309
{\pos(97.275)}Um...

527
00:37:09.394 --> 00:37:10.978
{\pos(97.275)}Okay. okay.
you got me.

528
00:37:11.062 --> 00:37:13.814
{\pos(97.275)}The dentist thing
is more of a hobby.

529
00:37:14.399 --> 00:37:16.817
{\pos(97.275)}In real life.
I am a spy.

530
00:37:17.318 --> 00:37:20.446
{\pos(97.275)}And it is top secret.
and you may not tell anybody.

531
00:37:20.530 --> 00:37:22.656
{\pos(97.275)}because if you do...
What does this do?

532
00:37:25.201 --> 00:37:26.201
{\pos(97.275)}(GASPS)

533
00:37:27.036 --> 00:37:28.036
{\pos(97.275)}Hey!
Oops.

534
00:37:28.496 --> 00:37:29.955
{\pos(97.275)}My unicorn!

535
00:37:30.290 --> 00:37:31.915
{\pos(97.275)}You have to fix it.

536
00:37:32.000 --> 00:37:34.918
{\pos(97.275)}Fix it?
Look. it has been
disintegrated.

537
00:37:35.003 --> 00:37:37.337
{\pos(97.275)}By definition.
it cannot be fixed.

538
00:37:37.839 --> 00:37:39.089
{\pos(97.275)}(GASPS)

539
00:37:39.340 --> 00:37:40.632
{\pos(97.275)}(INHALES)

540
00:37:42.635 --> 00:37:44.761
{\pos(97.275)}That's freaking me out.
What is she doing?

541
00:37:44.846 --> 00:37:48.056
{\pos(97.275)}She's gonna hold her breath
until she gets a new one.

542
00:37:49.434 --> 00:37:51.685
{\pos(97.275)}It is just a toy.
Now stop it!

543
00:37:51.769 --> 00:37:53.145
{\pos(97.275)}(GRUNTING)

544
00:37:55.106 --> 00:37:57.232
{\pos(97.275)}Okay. okay!
I'll fix it!

545
00:37:57.650 --> 00:37:59.610
{\pos(97.275)}Tim! Mark! Phil!

546
00:38:02.280 --> 00:38:03.489
{\pos(97.275)}This is very important.

547
00:38:03.573 --> 00:38:07.117
{\pos(97.275)}You have to get
the little girl
a new unicorn toy.

548
00:38:07.202 --> 00:38:08.160
{\pos(97.275)}Eh?

549
00:38:08.244 --> 00:38:10.245
{\pos(97.275)}(BOTH SPEAKING GIBBERISH)

550
00:38:12.040 --> 00:38:13.081
{\pos(97.275)}(CHUCKLING)

551
00:38:13.166 --> 00:38:15.042
{\pos(97.275)}Hey. hey. hey! A toy!

552
00:38:16.211 --> 00:38:18.295
{\pos(97.275)}Go. and hurry!

553
00:38:18.379 --> 00:38:19.588
{\pos(97.275)}What are those?

554
00:38:19.672 --> 00:38:22.841
{\pos(97.275)}They are my cousins.

555
00:38:23.676 --> 00:38:25.219
{\pos(97.275)}Jerry! Stuart!

556
00:38:26.304 --> 00:38:29.306
{\pos(97.275)}Watch them. and keep them
away from me. please.

557
00:38:46.574 --> 00:38:48.951
{\pos(97.275)}ALL: Wow!

558
00:38:52.830 --> 00:38:54.915
{\pos(97.275)}(ALL EXCLAIMING EXCITEDLY)

559
00:39:00.171 --> 00:39:01.588
{\pos(97.275)}(STUTTERING)

560
00:39:09.430 --> 00:39:10.430
{\pos(97.275)}(GROANS)

561
00:39:11.140 --> 00:39:12.266
{\pos(97.275)}Ooh!

562
00:39:14.727 --> 00:39:16.770
{\pos(97.275)}(SCREAMING)

563
00:39:25.321 --> 00:39:26.321
{\pos(97.275)}Oh!

564
00:39:26.406 --> 00:39:27.614
{\pos(97.275)}Hmm...

565
00:39:27.699 --> 00:39:28.699
{\pos(97.275)}(FEEDBACK)

566
00:39:28.825 --> 00:39:30.284
{\pos(97.275)}(SHUDDERING)

567
00:39:32.537 --> 00:39:34.955
{\pos(97.275)}(SINGING GIBBERISH)

568
00:39:40.169 --> 00:39:41.837
{\pos(97.275)}(ALL SINGING)

569
00:39:43.298 --> 00:39:44.881
{\pos(97.275)}(GIRLS GIGGLING)

570
00:39:44.966 --> 00:39:46.300
{\pos(97.275)}(CRASHING)

571
00:39:53.975 --> 00:39:55.142
{\pos(97.275)}It was your cousin's idea.

572
00:39:55.518 --> 00:39:56.643
{\pos(97.275)}What?

573
00:39:57.061 --> 00:39:58.562
{\pos(97.275)}Okay. bedtime.

574
00:39:58.646 --> 00:39:59.980
{\pos(97.275)}GIRLS: Aw!

575
00:40:00.398 --> 00:40:01.565
{\pos(97.275)}Aw!
Aw!

576
00:40:01.858 --> 00:40:03.275
{\pos(97.275)}Not you two!

577
00:40:03.359 --> 00:40:04.484
{\pos(97.275)}(CHEERING)

578
00:40:04.861 --> 00:40:09.573
{\pos(97.275)}Okey-dokey. Beddie-bye.
All tucked in. Sweet dreams.

579
00:40:11.492 --> 00:40:13.285
{\pos(97.275)}Just so you know.

580
00:40:13.369 --> 00:40:15.203
{\pos(97.275)}you're never
gonna be my dad.

581
00:40:15.288 --> 00:40:18.040
{\pos(97.275)}Hmm. I think
I can live with that.

582
00:40:19.709 --> 00:40:21.543
{\pos(97.275)}Are these beds
made out of bombs?

583
00:40:22.086 --> 00:40:26.256
{\pos(97.275)}Yes. but they are
very old and highly
unlikely to blow up.

584
00:40:27.175 --> 00:40:29.176
{\pos(97.275)}But try not to
toss and turn.

585
00:40:29.260 --> 00:40:30.427
{\pos(97.275)}Cool.

586
00:40:31.346 --> 00:40:34.514
{\pos(97.275)}Will you read us
a bedtime story?
No.

587
00:40:34.599 --> 00:40:37.684
{\pos(97.275)}But we can't go to sleep
without a bedtime story.

588
00:40:37.769 --> 00:40:41.396
{\pos(97.275)}Well. then it's going
to be a long night
for you. isn't it?

589
00:40:42.190 --> 00:40:45.817
{\pos(97.275)}So. good night.
sleep tight. and don't
let the bed bugs bite.

590
00:40:45.902 --> 00:40:49.821
{\pos(97.275)}Because there are literally
thousands of them.

591
00:40:50.865 --> 00:40:54.034
{\pos(97.275)}(WHISPERING SCARILY)
And there's probably
something in your closet.

592
00:40:55.620 --> 00:40:57.788
{\pos(97.275)}He's just kidding. Agnes.

593
00:41:00.958 --> 00:41:02.209
{\pos(97.275)}(DOOR OPENS)
(GASPS)

594
00:41:15.181 --> 00:41:16.890
{\pos(97.275)}(SPEAKS GIBBERISH)

595
00:41:20.019 --> 00:41:21.937
{\pos(97.275)}It's beautiful.

596
00:41:34.242 --> 00:41:35.575
{\pos(97.275)}(HUMMING)

597
00:41:35.827 --> 00:41:37.077
{\pos(97.275)}(SIGHS)

598
00:41:50.341 --> 00:41:52.801
{\pos(97.275)}Girls. let's go.

599
00:41:52.885 --> 00:41:55.721
{\pos(97.275)}Time to deliver the cookies!

600
00:41:55.805 --> 00:41:59.349
{\pos(97.275)}Mmm. Okay. But first.
we're going to dance class.

601
00:41:59.434 --> 00:42:02.352
{\pos(97.275)}Actually.
we're going to have to skip
the dance class today.

602
00:42:02.437 --> 00:42:04.271
{\pos(97.275)}Actually. we can't

603
00:42:04.355 --> 00:42:06.982
{\pos(97.275)}(IMITATING GRU)
Skip the dance
class today.

604
00:42:07.066 --> 00:42:09.025
{\pos(97.275)}We have a big recital
coming up.

605
00:42:09.110 --> 00:42:10.944
{\pos(97.275)}We're doing an excerpt
from Swan Lake.

606
00:42:11.028 --> 00:42:12.362
{\pos(97.275)}Yeah. Swan Lake!

607
00:42:12.447 --> 00:42:14.197
{\pos(97.275)}That's fantastic.
Wonderful.

608
00:42:14.282 --> 00:42:18.410
{\pos(97.275)}But we're going to
deliver cookies!
Come on!

609
00:42:20.580 --> 00:42:21.580
{\pos(97.275)}No.

610
00:42:22.457 --> 00:42:23.498
{\pos(97.275)}No?

611
00:42:23.583 --> 00:42:26.835
{\pos(97.275)}We're not going
to deliver cookies
until we do dance class.

612
00:42:26.919 --> 00:42:28.044
{\pos(97.275)}GRU: Really?

613
00:42:28.129 --> 00:42:31.840
{\pos(97.275)}Well. I am not driving you
to dance class.

614
00:42:31.924 --> 00:42:37.304
{\pos(97.275)}So if you want to go.
you are going to have
to walk yourselves.

615
00:42:43.394 --> 00:42:44.644
{\pos(97.275)}What are you doing?

616
00:42:44.729 --> 00:42:46.521
{\pos(97.275)}Walking to dance class.

617
00:42:46.606 --> 00:42:48.565
{\pos(97.275)}Ya? Okay. fine.

618
00:42:48.649 --> 00:42:52.486
{\pos(97.275)}You just keep walking.
because I'm really not
driving you!

619
00:42:52.570 --> 00:42:53.779
{\pos(97.275)}MARGO: Okay.

620
00:42:53.863 --> 00:42:54.863
{\pos(97.275)}(SIGHS IN FRUSTRATION)

621
00:42:55.281 --> 00:42:57.783
{\pos(97.275)}You're going to suffer
the wrath of Gru!

622
00:42:58.242 --> 00:43:00.243
{\pos(97.275)}Seriously.
I'm going to
count to three!

623
00:43:00.328 --> 00:43:02.287
{\pos(97.275)}And you had better
be in this car!

624
00:43:02.371 --> 00:43:06.041
{\pos(97.275)}Here we go! One! Two!

625
00:43:06.125 --> 00:43:09.711
{\pos(97.275)}INSTRUCTOR: Three.
four and five.

626
00:43:09.796 --> 00:43:12.672
{\pos(97.275)}And lift. and stretch.

627
00:43:12.757 --> 00:43:15.383
{\pos(97.275)}And one. and two...

628
00:43:15.468 --> 00:43:17.594
{\pos(97.275)}Here you go.
What is it?

629
00:43:17.678 --> 00:43:21.223
{\pos(97.275)}Your ticket
to the dance recital.
You are coming. right?

630
00:43:21.307 --> 00:43:22.933
{\pos(97.275)}Of course.
of course.

631
00:43:23.017 --> 00:43:26.102
{\pos(97.275)}I have pins and needles
that I'm sitting on.

632
00:43:26.187 --> 00:43:27.854
{\pos(97.275)}Pinky promise?

633
00:43:27.939 --> 00:43:29.231
{\pos(97.275)}(SIGHS)

634
00:43:29.315 --> 00:43:32.526
{\pos(97.275)}Oh. yes.
My pinky promises.

635
00:43:45.706 --> 00:43:50.377
{\pos(97.275)}All right.
Our first customer
is a man named Vector.

636
00:43:50.461 --> 00:43:52.212
{\pos(97.275)}But he's a V.

637
00:43:52.296 --> 00:43:54.297
{\pos(97.275)}You know. we're supposed
to start with the A's.

638
00:43:54.382 --> 00:43:56.299
{\pos(97.275)}Then we go to the B's.
Then we...

639
00:43:56.384 --> 00:43:58.802
{\pos(97.275)}Yes. yes!
I went to kindergarten.

640
00:43:58.886 --> 00:44:01.304
{\pos(97.275)}I know how
the alphabet works!

641
00:44:01.722 --> 00:44:03.098
{\pos(97.275)}(SIGHS)

642
00:44:03.891 --> 00:44:06.560
{\pos(97.275)}I was just thinking

643
00:44:06.644 --> 00:44:10.397
{\pos(97.275)}that it might be nice to
deliver Mr. Vector's first.

644
00:44:10.481 --> 00:44:12.148
{\pos(97.275)}That is all.

645
00:44:15.403 --> 00:44:17.904
{\pos(97.275)}Almost over.
It's almost over.

646
00:44:20.032 --> 00:44:24.286
{\pos(97.275)}Girls.
welcome back to the fortress
of Vector-tude! (CHUCKLING)

647
00:44:25.246 --> 00:44:27.747
{\pos(97.275)}Do you have
my cookies for me?

648
00:44:35.506 --> 00:44:37.424
{\pos(97.275)}Four boxes of mini-mints.
two toffee totes.

649
00:44:37.508 --> 00:44:42.220
{\pos(97.275)}two caramel clumpies
and fifteen boxes
of coco-nutties.

650
00:44:42.305 --> 00:44:45.891
{\pos(97.275)}Exactly.
I'd like to see somebody else
order that many cookies.

651
00:44:45.975 --> 00:44:47.017
{\pos(97.275)}Not likely.

652
00:44:47.101 --> 00:44:49.185
{\pos(97.275)}Name one person
who ordered more
cookies than me.

653
00:44:49.437 --> 00:44:50.979
{\pos(97.275)}That'll be $52.

654
00:44:51.564 --> 00:44:52.856
{\pos(97.275)}Right.

655
00:45:00.406 --> 00:45:03.116
{\pos(97.275)}Seven. eight. nine...

656
00:45:04.035 --> 00:45:06.578
{\pos(97.275)}Tic Tacs! Where was I?

657
00:45:06.662 --> 00:45:09.873
{\pos(97.275)}Seven. eight. nine...

658
00:45:09.957 --> 00:45:11.750
{\pos(97.275)}Why are you
wearing pajamas?

659
00:45:11.834 --> 00:45:16.129
{\pos(97.275)}(SCOFFING)
These aren't pajamas!
This is a warm-up suit.

660
00:45:23.429 --> 00:45:24.971
{\pos(97.275)}(BLEEPING)

661
00:45:32.813 --> 00:45:35.190
{\pos(97.275)}What are you
warming up for?
Stuff.

662
00:45:35.274 --> 00:45:36.274
{\pos(97.275)}What sort of stuff?

663
00:45:36.359 --> 00:45:38.777
{\pos(97.275)}Super-cool stuff
you wouldn't understand.

664
00:45:38.861 --> 00:45:40.278
{\pos(97.275)}Like sleeping?

665
00:45:40.363 --> 00:45:43.281
{\pos(97.275)}They are not pajamas!

666
00:45:51.165 --> 00:45:52.832
{\pos(97.275)}(ALL GRUNTING)

667
00:45:55.127 --> 00:45:58.338
{\pos(97.275)}Here you go. 52 big ones.

668
00:46:07.640 --> 00:46:08.932
{\pos(97.275)}(GASPS)

669
00:46:09.016 --> 00:46:10.684
{\pos(97.275)}(EXCLAIMS IN FRUSTRATION)

670
00:46:12.311 --> 00:46:13.687
{\pos(97.275)}(SCREAMING)

671
00:46:16.440 --> 00:46:17.899
{\pos(97.275)}Bye!

672
00:46:19.735 --> 00:46:21.653
{\pos(97.275)}(DEVICE POWERING DOWN)

673
00:46:27.493 --> 00:46:28.493
{\pos(97.275)}(GASPS)

674
00:46:40.715 --> 00:46:41.715
{\pos(97.275)}(EXHALES)

675
00:46:43.676 --> 00:46:44.634
{\pos(97.275)}(CRACKING)

676
00:46:44.719 --> 00:46:46.344
{\pos(97.275)}(SHUDDERING)

677
00:47:02.695 --> 00:47:05.321
{\pos(97.275)}(THEME MUSIC PLAYING ON TV)

678
00:47:09.285 --> 00:47:11.745
{\pos(97.275)}(MAN CHATTERING ON TV)

679
00:47:11.829 --> 00:47:13.204
{\pos(97.275)}(SOFTLY)
Come on!

680
00:47:27.136 --> 00:47:28.428
{\pos(97.275)}(GROANS)

681
00:47:35.269 --> 00:47:37.103
{\pos(97.275)}(GRUNTS) What the...

682
00:47:39.940 --> 00:47:41.608
{\pos(97.275)}Quiet down. fish!

683
00:47:48.616 --> 00:47:49.657
{\pos(97.275)}Down. boy!

684
00:48:11.305 --> 00:48:12.722
{\pos(97.275)}Ah-ha! (LAUGHING)

685
00:48:12.807 --> 00:48:16.142
{\pos(97.275)}We did it!
Come on. girls. let's go!

686
00:48:24.026 --> 00:48:27.111
{\pos(97.275)}But what about
the other people
who ordered cookies?

687
00:48:27.196 --> 00:48:29.906
{\pos(97.275)}Life is full of
disappointments

688
00:48:29.990 --> 00:48:32.742
{\pos(97.275)}for some people.
(CHUCKLING)

689
00:48:33.661 --> 00:48:35.161
{\pos(97.275)}(SCREAMING)
(EXCLAIMS)

690
00:48:36.080 --> 00:48:37.413
{\pos(97.275)}(SCREAMING)

691
00:48:37.498 --> 00:48:38.998
{\pos(97.275)}Don't do that!

692
00:48:39.083 --> 00:48:42.126
{\pos(97.275)}Super Silly Fun Land!
Can we go? Please?

693
00:48:42.545 --> 00:48:43.586
{\pos(97.275)}No.

694
00:48:43.671 --> 00:48:46.172
{\pos(97.275)}But we've never been.
And it's the funnest
place on earth!

695
00:48:46.257 --> 00:48:47.298
{\pos(97.275)}Don't care.

696
00:48:47.383 --> 00:48:48.508
{\pos(97.275)}Please?
Please?

697
00:48:48.592 --> 00:48:50.260
{\pos(97.275)}We'll never ask
for anything else.
ever again!

698
00:48:50.344 --> 00:48:52.387
{\pos(97.275)}Pretty please?
Please?

699
00:48:59.520 --> 00:49:01.479
{\pos(97.275)}Come on!
Come on!

700
00:49:02.022 --> 00:49:04.190
{\pos(97.275)}Light bulb.

701
00:49:09.113 --> 00:49:10.905
{\pos(97.275)}Come on!

702
00:49:10.990 --> 00:49:13.950
{\pos(97.275)}Goodbye. have fun.

703
00:49:17.371 --> 00:49:20.915
{\pos(97.275)}Sorry. dude.
They can't ride
without an adult.

704
00:49:21.000 --> 00:49:22.375
{\pos(97.275)}What?

705
00:49:22.459 --> 00:49:24.335
{\pos(97.275)}(SIGHS IN FRUSTRATION)

706
00:49:29.550 --> 00:49:32.010
{\pos(97.275)}(GIRLS WHOOPING)

707
00:49:36.348 --> 00:49:37.891
{\pos(97.275)}(ALL SCREAMING)

708
00:50:11.300 --> 00:50:12.967
{\pos(97.275)}(RETCHING)

709
00:50:18.891 --> 00:50:20.308
{\pos(97.275)}AGNES: (SQUEALS)
Oh. my gosh!

710
00:50:20.392 --> 00:50:22.810
{\pos(97.275)}Look at that
fluffy unicorn!

711
00:50:25.564 --> 00:50:27.857
{\pos(97.275)}He's so fluffy.
I'm gonna die!

712
00:50:27.942 --> 00:50:29.359
{\pos(97.275)}You've gotta let
us play for it!

713
00:50:29.443 --> 00:50:31.194
{\pos(97.275)}No. no. no.

714
00:50:31.278 --> 00:50:32.570
{\pos(97.275)}Come on!

715
00:50:34.114 --> 00:50:36.658
{\pos(97.275)}How much for
the fluffy unicorn?

716
00:50:36.742 --> 00:50:37.784
{\pos(97.275)}(LAUGHING)

717
00:50:37.868 --> 00:50:39.744
{\pos(97.275)}Well. it is not
for sale.

718
00:50:39.828 --> 00:50:41.746
{\pos(97.275)}But all you gotta do
to win it

719
00:50:41.830 --> 00:50:44.832
{\pos(97.275)}is knock down that
little spaceship there.

720
00:50:45.709 --> 00:50:46.834
{\pos(97.275)}It's easy!

721
00:50:55.219 --> 00:50:56.469
{\pos(97.275)}Yay!

722
00:51:08.482 --> 00:51:09.649
{\pos(97.275)}Again!

723
00:51:10.401 --> 00:51:12.819
{\pos(97.275)}Wait!
Come on.
One more time!

724
00:51:12.903 --> 00:51:14.070
{\pos(97.275)}Just one more.

725
00:51:14.154 --> 00:51:16.531
{\pos(97.275)}I accidentally
closed my eyes.

726
00:51:31.880 --> 00:51:33.881
{\pos(97.275)}I hit it!
I hit it!
That was cool.

727
00:51:35.551 --> 00:51:36.759
{\pos(97.275)}Aw!

728
00:51:38.345 --> 00:51:41.222
{\pos(97.275)}Whoa. whoa. whoa.
What was that?

729
00:51:41.974 --> 00:51:45.059
{\pos(97.275)}She hit that.
I saw that with
my own eyes.

730
00:51:45.144 --> 00:51:47.895
{\pos(97.275)}Hey. buddy.
let me explain
something to you.

731
00:51:47.980 --> 00:51:50.231
{\pos(97.275)}You see that
little tin spaceship?

732
00:51:50.315 --> 00:51:52.483
{\pos(97.275)}You see how
it's not knocked over?

733
00:51:52.568 --> 00:51:55.445
{\pos(97.275)}Do you know what
that means. professor?

734
00:51:55.529 --> 00:51:59.032
{\pos(97.275)}It means you don't
get the unicorn!

735
00:51:59.116 --> 00:52:01.117
{\pos(97.275)}Oh! Uh-oh!

736
00:52:01.201 --> 00:52:03.036
{\pos(97.275)}Somebody's got
a frowny face.

737
00:52:03.120 --> 00:52:05.538
{\pos(97.275)}Boo! Better luck
next time!

738
00:52:07.791 --> 00:52:10.501
{\pos(97.275)}Okay. my turn.

739
00:52:31.899 --> 00:52:34.442
{\pos(97.275)}Knocked over!

740
00:52:38.781 --> 00:52:40.573
{\pos(97.275)}It's so fluffy!

741
00:52:40.657 --> 00:52:41.657
{\pos(97.275)}Yeah!

742
00:52:42.326 --> 00:52:44.410
{\pos(97.275)}That was awesome!

743
00:52:44.495 --> 00:52:46.162
{\pos(97.275)}You blew up
the whole thing!

744
00:52:46.246 --> 00:52:48.623
{\pos(97.275)}Let's go.
Let's try
another game!

745
00:52:53.086 --> 00:52:54.587
{\pos(97.275)}(ALL LAUGHING)

746
00:52:55.672 --> 00:52:58.090
{\pos(97.275)}Gru. do you mind
if I have a quick word?

747
00:52:58.842 --> 00:53:01.093
{\pos(97.275)}Okay. girls. go play.

748
00:53:08.644 --> 00:53:10.937
{\pos(97.275)}I got the shrink ray!

749
00:53:13.565 --> 00:53:15.775
{\pos(97.275)}Cotton candy!

750
00:53:16.777 --> 00:53:20.696
{\pos(97.275)}We have 12 days
until the moon is
in optimum position.

751
00:53:20.781 --> 00:53:22.949
{\pos(97.275)}We can't afford
any distractions!

752
00:53:24.701 --> 00:53:25.952
{\pos(97.275)}Get me Perkins.

753
00:53:32.125 --> 00:53:33.292
{\pos(97.275)}Ah-ha!

754
00:53:33.961 --> 00:53:36.087
{\pos(97.275)}Sorry to bother you.
Mr. Perkins.

755
00:53:36.171 --> 00:53:40.174
{\pos(97.275)}but I figured that you
would want to see this!

756
00:53:40.968 --> 00:53:42.093
{\pos(97.275)}What?

757
00:53:54.606 --> 00:53:55.982
{\pos(97.275)}Well done. Gru.
(SQUEAKING)

758
00:53:56.066 --> 00:53:57.066
{\pos(97.275)}Rather impressive.

759
00:53:57.150 --> 00:54:00.152
{\pos(97.275)}Now. the rest
of the plan is simple.

760
00:54:00.821 --> 00:54:04.574
{\pos(97.275)}I fly to the moon.
I shrink the moon.

761
00:54:04.658 --> 00:54:08.369
{\pos(97.275)}I grab the moon.
I sit on the toilet.

762
00:54:08.453 --> 00:54:10.079
{\pos(97.275)}What?
(GIRLS LAUGHING)

763
00:54:10.163 --> 00:54:12.248
{\pos(97.275)}Sorry. Sorry!

764
00:54:12.332 --> 00:54:15.459
{\pos(97.275)}Could you excuse me
for just one second?

765
00:54:15.544 --> 00:54:16.961
{\pos(97.275)}I told you not
to touch my things.

766
00:54:17.045 --> 00:54:20.089
{\pos(97.275)}I told you. I told you.
I've told you
a thousand times.

767
00:54:20.173 --> 00:54:21.841
{\pos(97.275)}Hey. can we
order pizza?

768
00:54:21.925 --> 00:54:23.843
{\pos(97.275)}Pizza?
You just had lunch.

769
00:54:23.927 --> 00:54:25.094
{\pos(97.275)}Not now. for dinner.

770
00:54:25.178 --> 00:54:26.762
{\pos(97.275)}Dinner?

771
00:54:26.847 --> 00:54:29.640
{\pos(97.275)}Just...
Fine. fine. fine. whatever.
Just get back in there!

772
00:54:29.725 --> 00:54:31.559
{\pos(97.275)}Oh! Can we get
stuffed crust?

773
00:54:31.685 --> 00:54:32.727
{\pos(97.275)}(EXCLAIMING)

774
00:54:32.811 --> 00:54:34.020
{\pos(97.275)}Stuffed crust!
Stuffed crust!

775
00:54:34.104 --> 00:54:35.688
{\pos(97.275)}I'll stuff you
all in the crust!

776
00:54:35.772 --> 00:54:37.106
{\pos(97.275)}(GIGGLING)

777
00:54:37.691 --> 00:54:39.108
{\pos(97.275)}You're funny!

778
00:54:39.192 --> 00:54:41.944
{\pos(97.275)}Just don't come out
of that room again!

779
00:54:42.487 --> 00:54:43.529
{\pos(97.275)}All right.

780
00:54:44.448 --> 00:54:47.825
{\pos(97.275)}Sorry about that.
Where were we?

781
00:54:47.910 --> 00:54:49.493
{\pos(97.275)}You were sitting
on the toilet.

782
00:54:49.578 --> 00:54:54.123
{\pos(97.275)}No. no. no!
No. I'm sorry. It was
a little attempt at humor.

783
00:54:54.207 --> 00:54:57.043
{\pos(97.275)}I know how much
you like to laugh

784
00:54:59.504 --> 00:55:03.341
{\pos(97.275)}inside.
Now. I was saying...

785
00:55:03.467 --> 00:55:05.217
{\pos(97.275)}(DOOR CREAKING OPEN)

786
00:55:06.929 --> 00:55:08.846
{\pos(97.275)}You don't seem
terribly focused. Gru.

787
00:55:08.931 --> 00:55:11.265
{\pos(97.275)}Believe me.
I am completely focused.

788
00:55:11.391 --> 00:55:13.434
{\pos(97.275)}Hello! Whoa!
What?

789
00:55:13.518 --> 00:55:14.644
{\pos(97.275)}That guy is huge!

790
00:55:14.728 --> 00:55:16.145
{\pos(97.275)}Are we on TV?
What are those? Children?

791
00:55:16.229 --> 00:55:19.065
{\pos(97.275)}What are you doing?
I told you to stay
out of here!

792
00:55:19.149 --> 00:55:20.733
{\pos(97.275)}(GIRLS LAUGHING)

793
00:55:24.279 --> 00:55:25.488
{\pos(97.275)}No. no. no!

794
00:55:25.572 --> 00:55:26.656
{\pos(97.275)}Freeze ray!

795
00:55:26.740 --> 00:55:28.324
{\pos(97.275)}Mr. Gru?

796
00:55:28.408 --> 00:55:30.368
{\pos(97.275)}(GRU EXCLAIMING)

797
00:55:33.080 --> 00:55:34.413
{\pos(97.275)}Okay.

798
00:55:35.791 --> 00:55:37.166
{\pos(97.275)}As I was saying...

799
00:55:37.250 --> 00:55:41.087
{\pos(97.275)}No need to continue.
I've seen quite enough.

800
00:55:41.171 --> 00:55:42.338
{\pos(97.275)}But my plan...

801
00:55:42.422 --> 00:55:43.506
{\pos(97.275)}Is a great plan.

802
00:55:43.590 --> 00:55:46.801
{\pos(97.275)}I love everything
about your plan.
except for one thing.

803
00:55:47.678 --> 00:55:49.011
{\pos(97.275)}You.

804
00:55:52.265 --> 00:55:55.851
{\pos(97.275)}Look. Mom.
I drew a picture of me
landing on the moon!

805
00:55:56.895 --> 00:55:58.854
{\pos(97.275)}(EXCLAIMS INDIFFERENTLY)

806
00:55:58.939 --> 00:56:02.984
{\pos(97.275)}Look. Mom. I made
a prototype of the rocket
out of macaroni!

807
00:56:03.944 --> 00:56:05.236
{\pos(97.275)}(EXCLAIMS INDIFFERENTLY)

808
00:56:05.612 --> 00:56:07.571
{\pos(97.275)}Look. Mom.
I made a real rocket

809
00:56:07.656 --> 00:56:09.991
{\pos(97.275)}based on the
macaroni prototype!

810
00:56:12.285 --> 00:56:13.494
{\pos(97.275)}(GASPS)

811
00:56:14.204 --> 00:56:16.163
{\pos(97.275)}(EXCLAIMS INDIFFERENTLY)

812
00:56:21.253 --> 00:56:23.004
{\pos(97.275)}I don't understand.

813
00:56:23.338 --> 00:56:25.631
{\pos(97.275)}Let's face reality. Gru.

814
00:56:25.716 --> 00:56:30.469
{\pos(97.275)}You've been at this
for far too long with
far too little success.

815
00:56:30.679 --> 00:56:34.890
{\pos(97.275)}We're gonna put our faith.
our money. into a...

816
00:56:35.726 --> 00:56:37.351
{\pos(97.275)}Well. a younger villain.

817
00:56:37.436 --> 00:56:38.894
{\pos(97.275)}But I...

818
00:56:38.979 --> 00:56:41.105
{\pos(97.275)}It's over. Goodbye. Gru.

819
00:56:53.618 --> 00:56:55.494
{\pos(97.275)}(INDISTINCT MUTTERING)

820
00:56:56.830 --> 00:56:58.039
{\pos(97.275)}(SIGHS)

821
00:57:02.335 --> 00:57:06.839
{\pos(97.275)}Now. I know there have been
some rumors going around

822
00:57:06.923 --> 00:57:10.217
{\pos(97.275)}that the bank is
no longer funding us.

823
00:57:11.094 --> 00:57:13.888
{\pos(97.275)}Well. I am here to put
those rumors to rest.

824
00:57:16.016 --> 00:57:17.933
{\pos(97.275)}They are true.

825
00:57:18.018 --> 00:57:19.810
{\pos(97.275)}(ALL GASP)
Uh-oh!

826
00:57:19.895 --> 00:57:22.104
{\pos(97.275)}In terms of money.

827
00:57:23.273 --> 00:57:25.441
{\pos(97.275)}we have no money.

828
00:57:25.525 --> 00:57:28.110
{\pos(97.275)}So how will we
get to the moon?

829
00:57:29.279 --> 00:57:31.113
{\pos(97.275)}The answer is clear.

830
00:57:31.198 --> 00:57:32.782
{\pos(97.275)}We won't.

831
00:57:33.700 --> 00:57:34.992
{\pos(97.275)}(SOBBING)

832
00:57:35.827 --> 00:57:38.120
{\pos(97.275)}We are doomed.

833
00:57:39.372 --> 00:57:41.957
{\pos(97.275)}Now would probably
be a good time

834
00:57:42.042 --> 00:57:43.959
{\pos(97.275)}to look for other
employment options.

835
00:57:44.044 --> 00:57:45.377
{\pos(97.275)}(ALL GASP)

836
00:57:45.879 --> 00:57:46.962
{\pos(97.275)}I know.

837
00:57:47.047 --> 00:57:52.301
{\pos(97.275)}I have fired up my resume
as I suggest that
all of you do. as well.

838
00:57:53.303 --> 00:57:54.887
{\pos(97.275)}What is it?

839
00:57:56.807 --> 00:58:00.101
{\pos(97.275)}Can't you see that
I am in the middle
of a pep talk?

840
00:58:18.245 --> 00:58:19.995
{\pos(97.275)}(MINION EXCLAIMING)

841
00:58:20.413 --> 00:58:21.747
{\pos(97.275)}(LAUGHING)

842
00:58:21.915 --> 00:58:25.709
{\pos(97.275)}(ALL EXCLAIMING)

843
00:58:29.756 --> 00:58:31.132
{\pos(97.275)}Yes!

844
00:58:31.216 --> 00:58:34.135
{\pos(97.275)}Yes. we will build
our own rocket

845
00:58:34.761 --> 00:58:38.305
{\pos(97.275)}using this and whatever
else we can find!

846
00:58:38.765 --> 00:58:42.393
{\pos(97.275)}Grab everything!
Hit the junkyards!
Take apart the cars!

847
00:58:42.894 --> 00:58:44.770
{\pos(97.275)}Who needs the bank?

848
00:58:44.855 --> 00:58:46.605
{\pos(97.275)}Let's go. Let's go!

849
00:58:54.614 --> 00:58:56.615
{\pos(97.275)}(UPBEAT POP SONG PLAYING)

850
00:59:01.997 --> 00:59:03.247
{\pos(97.275)}(SCREAMING)

