00:04:31.897 --> 00:04:33.481
{\pos(289.275)}Despicable me

1273
00:04:58.548 --> 00:05:00.508
{\pos(289.275)}FRED: Morning. Gru!

1274
00:05:01.551 --> 00:05:02.927
{\pos(289.275)}(CHUCKLING)
How you doing?

1275
00:05:03.011 --> 00:05:05.054
{\pos(289.275)}Hello. Fred.

1276
00:05:05.138 --> 00:05:08.015
{\pos(289.275)}FYI. your dog
has been leaving

1277
00:05:08.100 --> 00:05:10.184
{\pos(289.275)}little bombs
all over my yard.

1278
00:05:10.268 --> 00:05:11.602
{\pos(289.275)}and I don't
appreciate it.

1279
00:05:11.687 --> 00:05:14.313
{\pos(289.275)}(LAUGHING) Sorry.
You know dogs.

1280
00:05:14.398 --> 00:05:16.065
{\pos(289.275)}They go wherever
they want to go.

1281
00:05:16.149 --> 00:05:17.900
{\pos(289.275)}Unless they're dead.

1282
00:05:18.443 --> 00:05:19.777
{\pos(289.275)}(LAUGHING)

1283
00:05:20.487 --> 00:05:21.612
{\pos(289.275)}I'm joking!

1284
00:05:22.739 --> 00:05:25.616
{\pos(289.275)}Although. it is true.
Anyway. have a good one.

1285
00:05:26.535 --> 00:05:29.161
{\pos(289.275)}Oh. okay.
Uh... Yeah.

1286
00:05:29.955 --> 00:05:33.165
{\pos(289.275)}Steamrolling whatever I see

1287
00:05:34.084 --> 00:05:35.501
{\pos(289.275)}Despicable me
(LOUD SNORING)

1288
00:05:35.919 --> 00:05:38.337
{\pos(289.275)}I'm having a bad. bad day

1289
00:05:38.422 --> 00:05:41.090
{\pos(289.275)}If you take it personal.
that's okay

1290
00:05:45.429 --> 00:05:47.096
{\pos(289.275)}Despicable me
(CONTINUES SNORING)

1291
00:05:50.475 --> 00:05:52.101
{\pos(289.275)}(DOORBELL CHIMES)

1292
00:05:52.269 --> 00:05:55.521
{\pos(289.275)}(GROANS)
You've got to be
pulling on my leg!

1293
00:05:59.443 --> 00:06:00.943
{\pos(289.275)}MARGO: Hello!

1294
00:06:01.570 --> 00:06:03.446
{\pos(289.275)}Cookies for sale.

1295
00:06:05.574 --> 00:06:07.783
{\pos(289.275)}Go away.
I'm not home.

1296
00:06:08.160 --> 00:06:10.619
{\pos(289.275)}Yes. you are.
I heard you.

1297
00:06:10.787 --> 00:06:14.498
{\pos(289.275)}(GASPS) No. you didn't. This

1298
00:06:14.583 --> 00:06:16.542
{\pos(289.275)}is a recording.

1299
00:06:16.626 --> 00:06:18.711
{\pos(289.275)}MARGO: No. it isn't.
Yes. it is.

1300
00:06:19.296 --> 00:06:23.507
{\pos(289.275)}Watch this.
Leave a message. beep.

1301
00:06:24.009 --> 00:06:25.801
{\pos(289.275)}(GRU SHOUTS IN PAIN)

1302
00:06:27.304 --> 00:06:29.096
{\pos(289.275)}Goodbye.
recorded message.

1303
00:06:29.181 --> 00:06:31.015
{\pos(289.275)}MARGO: Agnes.
come on.

1304
00:06:33.477 --> 00:06:34.518
{\pos(289.275)}Huh?

1305
00:06:39.983 --> 00:06:41.192
{\pos(289.275)}(SNAPS)

1306
00:06:41.318 --> 00:06:42.777
{\pos(289.275)}(SCREAMS) Kyle!

1307
00:06:42.861 --> 00:06:46.864
{\pos(289.275)}Bad dog! No!
No. no. Sit. My muffin.

1308
00:06:46.948 --> 00:06:48.115
{\pos(289.275)}Gru!

1309
00:06:48.784 --> 00:06:50.701
{\pos(289.275)}Ah. Dr. Nefario.

1310
00:06:50.869 --> 00:06:52.453
{\pos(289.275)}I know how you
must be feeling.

1311
00:06:52.537 --> 00:06:55.998
{\pos(289.275)}I. too. have encountered
great disappointment.

1312
00:06:56.666 --> 00:07:00.503
{\pos(289.275)}but in my eyes.
you will always be
one of the greats.

1313
00:07:01.171 --> 00:07:02.630
{\pos(289.275)}What? What happened?

1314
00:07:02.714 --> 00:07:04.131
{\pos(289.275)}It's all over the news!

1315
00:07:04.216 --> 00:07:06.258
{\pos(289.275)}Some fella just
stole a pyramid.

1316
00:07:06.343 --> 00:07:09.595
{\pos(289.275)}They're saying he makes
all other villains look

1317
00:07:10.388 --> 00:07:11.889
{\pos(289.275)}lame.

1318
00:07:14.226 --> 00:07:16.310
{\pos(289.275)}Assemble the minions!

1319
00:07:33.245 --> 00:07:34.453
{\pos(289.275)}(YELPS)

1320
00:07:45.006 --> 00:07:46.882
{\pos(289.275)}(COUNTING)

1321
00:07:46.967 --> 00:07:48.759
{\pos(289.275)}Minions. assemble!

1322
00:07:49.845 --> 00:07:51.262
{\pos(289.275)}Okay. Okay.

1323
00:07:53.348 --> 00:07:54.348
{\pos(289.275)}Throo...

1324
00:07:54.432 --> 00:07:56.058
{\pos(289.275)}(SCREAMS IN PAIN)

1325
00:07:58.353 --> 00:07:59.436
{\pos(289.275)}Hey!

1326
00:07:59.563 --> 00:08:01.313
{\pos(289.275)}(SPEAKING GIBBERISH)

1327
00:08:02.732 --> 00:08:04.150
{\pos(289.275)}(SPEAKING GIBBERISH)

1328
00:08:07.863 --> 00:08:09.738
{\pos(289.275)}(BOTH LAUGHING)

1329
00:08:13.034 --> 00:08:15.202
{\pos(289.275)}(ALL MUTTERING INDISTINCTLY)

1330
00:08:17.664 --> 00:08:19.999
{\pos(289.275)}(ALL SPEAKING GIBBERISH)

1331
00:08:39.769 --> 00:08:41.770
{\pos(289.275)}(ALL CHEERING)

1332
00:08:46.902 --> 00:08:49.528
{\pos(289.275)}Looking good. Kevin!
How is the family? Good?

1333
00:08:49.613 --> 00:08:50.863
{\pos(289.275)}All right.

1334
00:08:50.947 --> 00:08:53.949
{\pos(289.275)}That's my Billy boy!
What up. Larry?

1335
00:08:54.951 --> 00:08:56.994
{\pos(289.275)}Hello. everybody!

1336
00:08:57.078 --> 00:08:58.954
{\pos(289.275)}Yeah. all right!

1337
00:08:59.039 --> 00:09:01.373
{\pos(289.275)}Simmer down.
Simmer down!

1338
00:09:01.458 --> 00:09:03.375
{\pos(289.275)}Thank you. okay.

1339
00:09:03.460 --> 00:09:06.337
{\pos(289.275)}Now. I realize that
you guys probably heard

1340
00:09:06.630 --> 00:09:09.214
{\pos(289.275)}about this other villain
who stole the pyramids.

1341
00:09:09.299 --> 00:09:11.592
{\pos(289.275)}Apparently.
it's a big deal.

1342
00:09:11.676 --> 00:09:15.095
{\pos(289.275)}People are calling it
the crime of the century
and stuff like that.

1343
00:09:15.180 --> 00:09:19.350
{\pos(289.275)}But am I upset?
No. I am not!

1344
00:09:20.894 --> 00:09:22.269
{\pos(289.275)}A little.

1345
00:09:22.354 --> 00:09:26.315
{\pos(289.275)}but we have had
a pretty good year
ourselves.

1346
00:09:26.399 --> 00:09:29.234
{\pos(289.275)}and you guys are
all right in my book.

1347
00:09:29.319 --> 00:09:30.319
{\pos(289.275)}(EXCLAIMING)

1348
00:09:30.403 --> 00:09:31.654
{\pos(289.275)}No. no raises!

1349
00:09:31.738 --> 00:09:34.907
{\pos(289.275)}You're not going
to get any raises.

1350
00:09:35.784 --> 00:09:37.409
{\pos(289.275)}What did we do?

1351
00:09:37.494 --> 00:09:43.499
{\pos(289.275)}Well. we stole
the Times Square JumboTron!

1352
00:09:44.000 --> 00:09:45.209
{\pos(289.275)}Nice!
(ALL CHEERING)

1353
00:09:45.335 --> 00:09:46.794
{\pos(289.275)}Huh?

1354
00:09:46.878 --> 00:09:48.921
{\pos(289.275)}That's how I roll.

1355
00:09:49.339 --> 00:09:53.008
{\pos(289.275)}Yeah. you all like
watching football
on that. huh?

1356
00:09:53.843 --> 00:09:55.219
{\pos(289.275)}But that's not all.

1357
00:09:55.303 --> 00:09:58.597
{\pos(289.275)}We stole
the Statue of Liberty.

1358
00:09:58.682 --> 00:10:00.265
{\pos(289.275)}(ALL CHEERING)

1359
00:10:00.350 --> 00:10:02.685
{\pos(289.275)}The small one
from Las Vegas.

1360
00:10:02.769 --> 00:10:04.770
{\pos(289.275)}(EXCLAIMING DISAPPOINTEDLY)

1361
00:10:04.854 --> 00:10:08.857
{\pos(289.275)}And I won't even mention
the Eiffel Tower! Also Vegas.

1362
00:10:08.942 --> 00:10:11.735
{\pos(289.275)}Okay. I wasn't going to
tell you about this yet.

1363
00:10:11.820 --> 00:10:16.532
{\pos(289.275)}but I have been working
on something very big!

1364
00:10:17.409 --> 00:10:21.787
{\pos(289.275)}Something that will
blow this pyramid thing
out of the water!

1365
00:10:22.372 --> 00:10:26.709
{\pos(289.275)}And thanks to the efforts
of my good friend
Dr. Nefario...

1366
00:10:27.085 --> 00:10:28.127
{\pos(289.275)}Thank you!

1367
00:10:28.211 --> 00:10:29.920
{\pos(289.275)}GRU: Oh. there he is.

1368
00:10:30.005 --> 00:10:31.505
{\pos(289.275)}He's styling.

1369
00:10:32.090 --> 00:10:35.467
{\pos(289.275)}Now. we have located
a shrink ray

1370
00:10:35.552 --> 00:10:40.180
{\pos(289.275)}in a secret lab.
and once we take
this shrink ray.

1371
00:10:40.473 --> 00:10:43.642
{\pos(289.275)}we will have the capability

1372
00:10:43.727 --> 00:10:47.730
{\pos(289.275)}to pull off the true
crime of the century.

1373
00:10:48.481 --> 00:10:50.899
{\pos(289.275)}We are going to steal...

1374
00:10:53.445 --> 00:10:57.865
{\pos(289.275)}Wait. wait! I haven't
told you what it is yet.

1375
00:10:58.742 --> 00:11:00.034
{\pos(289.275)}(MINIONS EXCLAIMING)

1376
00:11:01.244 --> 00:11:02.244
{\pos(289.275)}Hey.

1377
00:11:02.328 --> 00:11:04.455
{\pos(289.275)}Dave. listen up. please.

1378
00:11:09.085 --> 00:11:12.504
{\pos(289.275)}Next. we are going to steal.

1379
00:11:12.589 --> 00:11:14.923
{\pos(289.275)}(SOFTLY) pause for effect.

1380
00:11:15.759 --> 00:11:17.676
{\pos(289.275)}the moon!

1381
00:11:17.761 --> 00:11:19.053
{\pos(289.275)}(MINIONS CHEERING)

1382
00:11:19.137 --> 00:11:22.973
{\pos(289.275)}And once the moon is mine.

1383
00:11:23.433 --> 00:11:27.770
{\pos(289.275)}the world will give me
whatever I want
to get it back!

1384
00:11:27.854 --> 00:11:33.192
{\pos(289.275)}And I will be
the greatest villain
of all time!

1385
00:11:36.237 --> 00:11:39.698
{\pos(289.275)}That's what
I'm talking about.

1386
00:11:39.783 --> 00:11:41.575
{\pos(289.275)}(CELL PHONE RINGING)

1387
00:11:42.035 --> 00:11:43.077
{\pos(289.275)}Yes?

1388
00:11:43.244 --> 00:11:46.955
{\pos(289.275)}Hello. Gru? I've been
crunching some numbers.

1389
00:11:47.040 --> 00:11:50.209
{\pos(289.275)}and I really don't see
how we can afford this.

1390
00:11:50.293 --> 00:11:53.128
{\pos(289.275)}It can't be done.
I'm not a miracle worker.

1391
00:11:53.588 --> 00:11:55.172
{\pos(289.275)}Hey. chillax.

1392
00:11:55.256 --> 00:11:58.926
{\pos(289.275)}I'll just get another loan
from the bank. They love me!

1393
00:12:13.233 --> 00:12:14.483
{\pos(289.275)}(EXCLAIMS)

1394
00:12:14.567 --> 00:12:16.276
{\pos(289.275)}Edith. stop it!

1395
00:12:16.361 --> 00:12:18.487
{\pos(289.275)}What? I'm just walking.

1396
00:12:26.162 --> 00:12:27.704
{\pos(289.275)}(KEYS CLACKING)

1397
00:12:31.292 --> 00:12:33.377
{\pos(289.275)}ALL: Hi. Miss Hattie.
We're back.

1398
00:12:36.256 --> 00:12:37.756
{\pos(289.275)}Hello. girls!

1399
00:12:37.841 --> 00:12:40.676
{\pos(289.275)}Anybody come to adopt us
while we were out?

1400
00:12:40.844 --> 00:12:43.637
{\pos(289.275)}Mmm. Let me think.

1401
00:12:44.097 --> 00:12:45.180
{\pos(289.275)}No!

1402
00:12:48.393 --> 00:12:51.520
{\pos(289.275)}Edith! What did you
put on my desk?

1403
00:12:51.896 --> 00:12:53.564
{\pos(289.275)}A mud pie.

1404
00:12:53.648 --> 00:12:58.235
{\pos(289.275)}(SIGHS) You're never
gonna get adopted. Edith.
You know that. don't you?

1405
00:12:58.319 --> 00:12:59.778
{\pos(289.275)}Yeah. I know.

1406
00:12:59.863 --> 00:13:00.863
{\pos(289.275)}Good.

1407
00:13:00.947 --> 00:13:04.324
{\pos(289.275)}So. how did it go. girls?
Did we meet our quotas?

1408
00:13:05.160 --> 00:13:06.451
{\pos(289.275)}Sort of.

1409
00:13:06.536 --> 00:13:10.789
{\pos(289.275)}We sold 43 mini-mints.
30 choco-swirlies.
and 18 coco-nutties.

1410
00:13:12.709 --> 00:13:14.877
{\pos(289.275)}(SIGHS) Okay.

1411
00:13:15.253 --> 00:13:19.131
{\pos(289.275)}Well. you say that like
it's a great sale day.

1412
00:13:19.215 --> 00:13:21.383
{\pos(289.275)}Look at my face!

1413
00:13:21.467 --> 00:13:24.720
{\pos(289.275)}Do you still think
it's a great sale day?

1414
00:13:25.638 --> 00:13:27.639
{\pos(289.275)}Eighteen coco-nutties.

1415
00:13:28.057 --> 00:13:32.728
{\pos(289.275)}I think we can do a little
better than that. don't you?

1416
00:13:33.563 --> 00:13:34.605
{\pos(289.275)}Yeah.

1417
00:13:34.689 --> 00:13:39.067
{\pos(289.275)}We wouldn't want to spend
the weekend in the
Box of Shame. would we? No.

1418
00:13:39.485 --> 00:13:40.652
{\pos(289.275)}ALL: No. Miss Hattie.

1419
00:13:40.737 --> 00:13:44.448
{\pos(289.275)}Okay. good. Off you go.
Go clean something of mine.

1420
00:13:46.534 --> 00:13:47.743
{\pos(289.275)}Hi. Penny.
Hi. Penny.

1421
00:13:47.827 --> 00:13:48.994
{\pos(289.275)}Hi. guys.

1422
00:13:52.874 --> 00:13:53.874
{\pos(289.275)}(CELL PHONE RINGING)

1423
00:13:53.958 --> 00:13:57.169
{\pos(289.275)}Hello. Mom. Sorry.
I meant to call. but...

1424
00:13:57.545 --> 00:14:00.797
{\pos(289.275)}I just wanted to
congratulate you
on stealing the pyramid.

1425
00:14:01.132 --> 00:14:03.258
{\pos(289.275)}(SIGHING)
That was you.
wasn't it?

1426
00:14:03.593 --> 00:14:07.763
{\pos(289.275)}Or was it a villain
who's actually successful?
(LAUGHING)

1427
00:14:08.264 --> 00:14:11.016
{\pos(289.275)}Just so you know. Mom.
I am about to do something

1428
00:14:11.100 --> 00:14:13.894
{\pos(289.275)}that's very. very big.
very important.

1429
00:14:14.270 --> 00:14:17.022
{\pos(289.275)}When you hear about it.
you're going to be
very proud.

1430
00:14:17.357 --> 00:14:18.482
{\pos(289.275)}(SCOFFS)

1431
00:14:18.566 --> 00:14:21.777
{\pos(289.275)}Good luck with that.
Okay. I'm out of here.

1432
00:14:23.279 --> 00:14:24.947
{\pos(289.275)}(GRUNTING)

1433
00:15:06.990 --> 00:15:08.657
{\pos(289.275)}(BREATHES DEEPLY)

1434
00:15:30.096 --> 00:15:32.180
{\pos(289.275)}Gru to see Mr. Perkins.

1435
00:15:32.640 --> 00:15:34.683
{\pos(289.275)}Yes. please have a seat.

1436
00:15:46.279 --> 00:15:49.072
{\pos(289.275)}NEIL ARMSTRONG: That's one
small step for man.

1437
00:15:51.576 --> 00:15:53.326
{\pos(289.275)}one giant leap for mankind.

1438
00:15:53.411 --> 00:15:56.204
{\pos(289.275)}Ma. someday I'm going
to go to the moon.

1439
00:15:56.330 --> 00:15:59.166
{\pos(289.275)}(SCOFFS) I'm afraid
you're too late. Son.

1440
00:15:59.500 --> 00:16:01.918
{\pos(289.275)}NASA isn't sending
the monkeys anymore.

1441
00:16:10.678 --> 00:16:11.720
{\pos(289.275)}Hey.

1442
00:16:19.145 --> 00:16:23.356
{\pos(289.275)}I'm applying
for a new villain loan.
Go by the name of Vector.

1443
00:16:27.945 --> 00:16:29.446
{\pos(289.275)}It's a mathematical term.

1444
00:16:29.530 --> 00:16:34.034
{\pos(289.275)}a quantity represented
by an arrow. with both
direction and magnitude.

1445
00:16:38.039 --> 00:16:40.040
{\pos(289.275)}Vector! That's me.

1446
00:16:40.124 --> 00:16:45.378
{\pos(289.275)}'cause I'm committing
crimes with both
direction and magnitude.

1447
00:16:45.463 --> 00:16:47.130
{\pos(289.275)}Oh. yeah!

1448
00:16:49.258 --> 00:16:50.842
{\pos(289.275)}Check out
my new weapon.

1449
00:16:50.927 --> 00:16:53.178
{\pos(289.275)}Piranha gun! Oh. yes!

1450
00:16:53.262 --> 00:16:55.388
{\pos(289.275)}Fires live piranhas.
Ever seen one before?

1451
00:16:55.473 --> 00:16:57.057
{\pos(289.275)}No. you haven't.
I invented it.

1452
00:16:57.141 --> 00:16:59.309
{\pos(289.275)}Do you want
a demonstration?

1453
00:16:59.811 --> 00:17:02.354
{\pos(289.275)}Oh! Shoot!
So difficult.
sometimes.

1454
00:17:02.438 --> 00:17:04.523
{\pos(289.275)}to get the piranha
back inside of my...
(EXCLAIMS)

1455
00:17:04.607 --> 00:17:07.109
{\pos(289.275)}RECEPTIONIST: Mr. Gru.
Mr. Perkins will see you now.

1456
00:17:08.111 --> 00:17:09.277
{\pos(289.275)}GRU: So. all I need

1457
00:17:09.362 --> 00:17:12.364
{\pos(289.275)}is money from the bank
to build a rocket.

1458
00:17:12.448 --> 00:17:15.450
{\pos(289.275)}And then.
the moon is ours.
Wow!

1459
00:17:16.327 --> 00:17:18.203
{\pos(289.275)}Well. very nice
presentation.

1460
00:17:18.287 --> 00:17:20.539
{\pos(289.275)}I'd like to see
this shrink ray.

1461
00:17:20.623 --> 00:17:23.333
{\pos(289.275)}Absolutely! Will do.

1462
00:17:23.417 --> 00:17:24.793
{\pos(289.275)}(SOFTLY)
Soon as I have it.

1463
00:17:25.837 --> 00:17:27.796
{\pos(289.275)}You don't have it?

1464
00:17:27.880 --> 00:17:31.383
{\pos(289.275)}And yet you have
the audacity to ask
the bank for money?

1465
00:17:32.593 --> 00:17:34.136
{\pos(289.275)}Apparently.

1466
00:17:34.220 --> 00:17:38.557
{\pos(289.275)}Do you have any idea
of the capital that this bank
has invested in you. Gru?

1467
00:17:39.600 --> 00:17:44.229
{\pos(289.275)}With far too few
of your sinister plots
actually turning a profit.

1468
00:17:45.064 --> 00:17:48.900
{\pos(289.275)}How can I put it?
Let's say this apple is you.

1469
00:17:49.485 --> 00:17:51.987
{\pos(289.275)}If we don't start
getting our money back...

1470
00:17:53.823 --> 00:17:55.490
{\pos(289.275)}Get the picture?

1471
00:17:56.909 --> 00:18:00.495
{\pos(289.275)}Look. Gru. the point is.
there are a lot of
new villains out there.

1472
00:18:00.830 --> 00:18:03.623
{\pos(289.275)}younger than you.
hungrier than you.

1473
00:18:03.708 --> 00:18:05.750
{\pos(289.275)}younger than you.

1474
00:18:05.835 --> 00:18:08.086
{\pos(289.275)}Like that young fellow
out there named Vector.

1475
00:18:08.171 --> 00:18:09.838
{\pos(289.275)}He just stole a pyramid!

1476
00:18:14.343 --> 00:18:16.428
