1684
00:33:02.731 --> 00:33:04.773
{\pos(289.275)}Yes. you may
touch the floor.

1685
00:33:04.858 --> 00:33:06.233
{\pos(289.275)}What about the air?

1686
00:33:06.318 --> 00:33:08.402
{\pos(289.275)}Yes. you may
touch the air!

1687
00:33:08.487 --> 00:33:09.528
{\pos(289.275)}What about this?

1688
00:33:10.906 --> 00:33:12.239
{\pos(289.275)}(EXCLAIMS)

1689
00:33:12.699 --> 00:33:14.658
{\pos(289.275)}Where did you get that?
Found it.

1690
00:33:14.743 --> 00:33:18.496
{\pos(289.275)}Okay. Rule number two.
You will not bother me
while I'm working.

1691
00:33:18.580 --> 00:33:20.498
{\pos(289.275)}Rule number three.

1692
00:33:20.582 --> 00:33:25.044
{\pos(289.275)}You will not cry or whine
or laugh or giggle

1693
00:33:25.378 --> 00:33:27.755
{\pos(289.275)}or sneeze
or burp or fart!

1694
00:33:28.423 --> 00:33:32.760
{\pos(289.275)}So. no. no. no
annoying sounds.
All right?

1695
00:33:32.844 --> 00:33:34.678
{\pos(289.275)}Does this count
as annoying?

1696
00:33:34.763 --> 00:33:36.430
{\pos(289.275)}(POPPING)

1697
00:33:38.433 --> 00:33:39.600
{\pos(289.275)}Very!

1698
00:33:40.101 --> 00:33:41.310
{\pos(289.275)}(SIGHS)

1699
00:33:42.103 --> 00:33:44.688
{\pos(289.275)}I will see you
in six hours.

1700
00:33:46.775 --> 00:33:50.694
{\pos(289.275)}Okay. don't worry.
Everything's going
to be fine.

1701
00:33:51.321 --> 00:33:55.699
{\pos(289.275)}We're gonna be
really happy here.
Right? Agnes?

1702
00:33:57.118 --> 00:33:58.327
{\pos(289.275)}Mmm?

1703
00:34:00.956 --> 00:34:01.956
{\pos(289.275)}(EXCLAIMS)

1704
00:34:02.457 --> 00:34:04.291
{\pos(289.275)}(SPEAKING GIBBERISH)

1705
00:34:05.669 --> 00:34:07.378
{\pos(289.275)}(CLICKING)

1706
00:34:09.506 --> 00:34:11.549
{\pos(289.275)}(UPBEAT POP MUSIC PLAYING)

1707
00:34:23.478 --> 00:34:27.273
{\pos(289.275)}Uh. question.
What are these?

1708
00:34:28.191 --> 00:34:32.653
{\pos(289.275)}A dozen boogie robots!
Boogie! (LAUGHING)

1709
00:34:32.737 --> 00:34:34.738
{\pos(289.275)}Look at this. Watch me!

1710
00:34:34.823 --> 00:34:36.323
{\pos(289.275)}(MUSIC STOPS)

1711
00:34:38.660 --> 00:34:41.328
{\pos(289.275)}Cookie robots.
I said cookie robots.

1712
00:34:41.913 --> 00:34:44.498
{\pos(289.275)}Why are you so old?

1713
00:34:46.960 --> 00:34:48.586
{\pos(289.275)}Okay. I'm on it.

1714
00:34:49.504 --> 00:34:50.838
{\pos(289.275)}Hello?

1715
00:35:06.521 --> 00:35:07.771
{\pos(289.275)}TV!

1716
00:35:09.274 --> 00:35:11.150
{\pos(289.275)}(KYLE GROWLING)

1717
00:35:25.832 --> 00:35:27.166
{\pos(289.275)}(WHIMPERS)

1718
00:35:27.626 --> 00:35:28.626
{\pos(289.275)}MARGO: What is that?

1719
00:35:28.710 --> 00:35:29.918
{\pos(289.275)}Wow!
Look at that!

1720
00:35:30.003 --> 00:35:31.462
{\pos(289.275)}That is cool!

1721
00:35:32.297 --> 00:35:33.589
{\pos(289.275)}Come on!

1722
00:35:34.090 --> 00:35:36.383
{\pos(289.275)}I don't think
he's a dentist.

1723
00:35:43.767 --> 00:35:45.059
{\pos(289.275)}(WHIMPERS)

1724
00:35:50.231 --> 00:35:52.024
{\pos(289.275)}We've been working
on this for a while.

1725
00:35:52.108 --> 00:35:54.902
{\pos(289.275)}It's a anti-gravity serum.

1726
00:35:56.154 --> 00:35:57.571
{\pos(289.275)}(EXCLAIMING)

1727
00:35:58.031 --> 00:35:59.365
{\pos(289.275)}(SCREAMING)

1728
00:36:00.617 --> 00:36:03.994
{\pos(289.275)}I meant to close that.
He'll be all right.
I'm sure.

1729
00:36:04.079 --> 00:36:05.621
{\pos(289.275)}Do the effects wear off?

1730
00:36:05.705 --> 00:36:07.164
{\pos(289.275)}Uh. so far.

1731
00:36:07.248 --> 00:36:09.249
{\pos(289.275)}no. No. they don't.

1732
00:36:10.794 --> 00:36:13.879
{\pos(289.275)}And here. of course.
is the new weapon
you ordered.

1733
00:36:14.005 --> 00:36:15.464
{\pos(289.275)}(FARTING)

1734
00:36:17.550 --> 00:36:18.509
{\pos(289.275)}No. no.

1735
00:36:18.593 --> 00:36:22.471
{\pos(289.275)}I said "dart gun."
not... Okay.

1736
00:36:23.098 --> 00:36:25.849
{\pos(289.275)}Oh. yes.
'Cause I was wondering

1737
00:36:25.934 --> 00:36:28.519
{\pos(289.275)}under what circumstances
would we use this?

1738
00:36:28.603 --> 00:36:30.062
{\pos(289.275)}But. anyway.

1739
00:36:30.146 --> 00:36:33.607
{\pos(289.275)}What I really wanted
to show you was this.

1740
00:36:38.363 --> 00:36:41.490
{\pos(289.275)}Now those are
cookie robots!

1741
00:36:42.617 --> 00:36:45.869
{\pos(289.275)}AGNES: (SINGING)
La. la. la. la
I love unicorns

1742
00:36:45.954 --> 00:36:49.623
{\pos(289.275)}What are you doing here?
I told you to stay
in the kitchen!

1743
00:36:49.708 --> 00:36:52.292
{\pos(289.275)}We got bored.
What is this place?

1744
00:36:52.544 --> 00:36:54.211
{\pos(289.275)}Can I drink this?

1745
00:36:54.295 --> 00:36:56.755
{\pos(289.275)}Do you want to explode?

1746
00:36:57.215 --> 00:36:58.298
{\pos(289.275)}(EXCLAIMS)

1747
00:36:58.383 --> 00:36:59.383
{\pos(289.275)}Gru!

1748
00:36:59.467 --> 00:37:01.468
{\pos(289.275)}Get back
in the kitchen!

1749
00:37:01.553 --> 00:37:03.679
{\pos(289.275)}Will you play with us?
No.

1750
00:37:04.097 --> 00:37:06.306
{\pos(289.275)}Why?
Because I'm busy.

1751
00:37:06.391 --> 00:37:07.933
{\pos(289.275)}(SCOFFS)
Doing what?

1752
00:37:08.017 --> 00:37:09.309
{\pos(289.275)}Um...

1753
00:37:09.394 --> 00:37:10.978
{\pos(289.275)}Okay. okay.
you got me.

1754
00:37:11.062 --> 00:37:13.814
{\pos(289.275)}The dentist thing
is more of a hobby.

1755
00:37:14.399 --> 00:37:16.817
{\pos(289.275)}In real life.
I am a spy.

1756
00:37:17.318 --> 00:37:20.446
{\pos(289.275)}And it is top secret.
and you may not tell anybody.

1757
00:37:20.530 --> 00:37:22.656
{\pos(289.275)}because if you do...
What does this do?

1758
00:37:25.201 --> 00:37:26.201
{\pos(289.275)}(GASPS)

1759
00:37:27.036 --> 00:37:28.036
{\pos(289.275)}Hey!
Oops.

1760
00:37:28.496 --> 00:37:29.955
{\pos(289.275)}My unicorn!

1761
00:37:30.290 --> 00:37:31.915
{\pos(289.275)}You have to fix it.

1762
00:37:32.000 --> 00:37:34.918
{\pos(289.275)}Fix it?
Look. it has been
disintegrated.

1763
00:37:35.003 --> 00:37:37.337
{\pos(289.275)}By definition.
it cannot be fixed.

1764
00:37:37.839 --> 00:37:39.089
{\pos(289.275)}(GASPS)

1765
00:37:39.340 --> 00:37:40.632
{\pos(289.275)}(INHALES)

1766
00:37:42.635 --> 00:37:44.761
{\pos(289.275)}That's freaking me out.
What is she doing?

1767
00:37:44.846 --> 00:37:48.056
{\pos(289.275)}She's gonna hold her breath
until she gets a new one.

1768
00:37:49.434 --> 00:37:51.685
{\pos(289.275)}It is just a toy.
Now stop it!

1769
00:37:51.769 --> 00:37:53.145
{\pos(289.275)}(GRUNTING)

1770
00:37:55.106 --> 00:37:57.232
{\pos(289.275)}Okay. okay!
I'll fix it!

1771
00:37:57.650 --> 00:37:59.610
{\pos(289.275)}Tim! Mark! Phil!

1772
00:38:02.280 --> 00:38:03.489
{\pos(289.275)}This is very important.

1773
00:38:03.573 --> 00:38:07.117
{\pos(289.275)}You have to get
the little girl
a new unicorn toy.

1774
00:38:07.202 --> 00:38:08.160
{\pos(289.275)}Eh?

1775
00:38:08.244 --> 00:38:10.245
{\pos(289.275)}(BOTH SPEAKING GIBBERISH)

1776
00:38:12.040 --> 00:38:13.081
{\pos(289.275)}(CHUCKLING)

1777
00:38:13.166 --> 00:38:15.042
{\pos(289.275)}Hey. hey. hey! A toy!

1778
00:38:16.211 --> 00:38:18.295
{\pos(289.275)}Go. and hurry!

1779
00:38:18.379 --> 00:38:19.588
{\pos(289.275)}What are those?

1780
00:38:19.672 --> 00:38:22.841
{\pos(289.275)}They are my cousins.

1781
00:38:23.676 --> 00:38:25.219
{\pos(289.275)}Jerry! Stuart!

1782
00:38:26.304 --> 00:38:29.306
{\pos(289.275)}Watch them. and keep them
away from me. please.

1783
00:38:46.574 --> 00:38:48.951
{\pos(289.275)}ALL: Wow!

1784
00:38:52.830 --> 00:38:54.915
{\pos(289.275)}(ALL EXCLAIMING EXCITEDLY)

1785
00:39:00.171 --> 00:39:01.588
{\pos(289.275)}(STUTTERING)

1786
00:39:09.430 --> 00:39:10.430
{\pos(289.275)}(GROANS)

1787
00:39:11.140 --> 00:39:12.266
{\pos(289.275)}Ooh!

1788
00:39:14.727 --> 00:39:16.770
{\pos(289.275)}(SCREAMING)

1789
00:39:25.321 --> 00:39:26.321
{\pos(289.275)}Oh!

1790
00:39:26.406 --> 00:39:27.614
{\pos(289.275)}Hmm...

1791
00:39:27.699 --> 00:39:28.699
{\pos(289.275)}(FEEDBACK)

1792
00:39:28.825 --> 00:39:30.284
{\pos(289.275)}(SHUDDERING)

1793
00:39:32.537 --> 00:39:34.955
{\pos(289.275)}(SINGING GIBBERISH)

1794
00:39:40.169 --> 00:39:41.837
{\pos(289.275)}(ALL SINGING)

1795
00:39:43.298 --> 00:39:44.881
{\pos(289.275)}(GIRLS GIGGLING)

1796
00:39:44.966 --> 00:39:46.300
{\pos(289.275)}(CRASHING)

1797
00:39:53.975 --> 00:39:55.142
{\pos(289.275)}It was your cousin's idea.

1798
00:39:55.518 --> 00:39:56.643
{\pos(289.275)}What?

1799
00:39:57.061 --> 00:39:58.562
{\pos(289.275)}Okay. bedtime.

1800
00:39:58.646 --> 00:39:59.980
{\pos(289.275)}GIRLS: Aw!

1801
00:40:00.398 --> 00:40:01.565
{\pos(289.275)}Aw!
Aw!

1802
00:40:01.858 --> 00:40:03.275
{\pos(289.275)}Not you two!

1803
00:40:03.359 --> 00:40:04.484
{\pos(289.275)}(CHEERING)

1804
00:40:04.861 --> 00:40:09.573
{\pos(289.275)}Okey-dokey. Beddie-bye.
All tucked in. Sweet dreams.

1805
00:40:11.492 --> 00:40:13.285
{\pos(289.275)}Just so you know.

1806
00:40:13.369 --> 00:40:15.203
{\pos(289.275)}you're never
gonna be my dad.

1807
00:40:15.288 --> 00:40:18.040
{\pos(289.275)}Hmm. I think
I can live with that.

1808
00:40:19.709 --> 00:40:21.543
{\pos(289.275)}Are these beds
made out of bombs?

1809
00:40:22.086 --> 00:40:26.256
{\pos(289.275)}Yes. but they are
very old and highly
unlikely to blow up.

1810
00:40:27.175 --> 00:40:29.176
{\pos(289.275)}But try not to
toss and turn.

1811
00:40:29.260 --> 00:40:30.427
{\pos(289.275)}Cool.

1812
00:40:31.346 --> 00:40:34.514
{\pos(289.275)}Will you read us
a bedtime story?
No.

1813
00:40:34.599 --> 00:40:37.684
{\pos(289.275)}But we can't go to sleep
without a bedtime story.

1814
00:40:37.769 --> 00:40:41.396
{\pos(289.275)}Well. then it's going
to be a long night
for you. isn't it?

1815
00:40:42.190 --> 00:40:45.817
{\pos(289.275)}So. good night.
sleep tight. and don't
let the bed bugs bite.

1816
00:40:45.902 --> 00:40:49.821
{\pos(289.275)}Because there are literally
thousands of them.

1817
00:40:50.865 --> 00:40:54.034
{\pos(289.275)}(WHISPERING SCARILY)
And there's probably
something in your closet.

1818
00:40:55.620 --> 00:40:57.788
{\pos(289.275)}He's just kidding. Agnes.

1819
00:41:00.958 --> 00:41:02.209
{\pos(289.275)}(DOOR OPENS)
(GASPS)

1820
00:41:15.181 --> 00:41:16.890
{\pos(289.275)}(SPEAKS GIBBERISH)

1821
00:41:20.019 --> 00:41:21.937
{\pos(289.275)}It's beautiful.

1822
00:41:34.242 --> 00:41:35.575
{\pos(289.275)}(HUMMING)

1823
00:41:35.827 --> 00:41:37.077
{\pos(289.275)}(SIGHS)

1824
00:41:50.341 --> 00:41:52.801
{\pos(289.275)}Girls. let's go.

1825
00:41:52.885 --> 00:41:55.721
{\pos(289.275)}Time to deliver the cookies!

1826
00:41:55.805 --> 00:41:59.349
{\pos(289.275)}Mmm. Okay. But first.
we're going to dance class.

1827
00:41:59.434 --> 00:42:02.352
{\pos(289.275)}Actually.
we're going to have to skip
the dance class today.

1828
00:42:02.437 --> 00:42:04.271
{\pos(289.275)}Actually. we can't

1829
00:42:04.355 --> 00:42:06.982
{\pos(289.275)}(IMITATING GRU)
Skip the dance
class today.

1830
00:42:07.066 --> 00:42:09.025
{\pos(289.275)}We have a big recital
coming up.

1831
00:42:09.110 --> 00:42:10.944
{\pos(289.275)}We're doing an excerpt
from Swan Lake.

1832
00:42:11.028 --> 00:42:12.362
{\pos(289.275)}Yeah. Swan Lake!

1833
00:42:12.447 --> 00:42:14.197
{\pos(289.275)}That's fantastic.
Wonderful.

1834
00:42:14.282 --> 00:42:18.410
{\pos(289.275)}But we're going to
deliver cookies!
Come on!

1835
00:42:20.580 --> 00:42:21.580
{\pos(289.275)}No.

1836
00:42:22.457 --> 00:42:23.498
{\pos(289.275)}No?

1837
00:42:23.583 --> 00:42:26.835
{\pos(289.275)}We're not going
to deliver cookies
until we do dance class.

1838
00:42:26.919 --> 00:42:28.044
{\pos(289.275)}GRU: Really?

1839
00:42:28.129 --> 00:42:31.840
{\pos(289.275)}Well. I am not driving you
to dance class.

1840
00:42:31.924 --> 00:42:37.304
{\pos(289.275)}So if you want to go.
you are going to have
to walk yourselves.

1841
00:42:43.394 --> 00:42:44.644
{\pos(289.275)}What are you doing?

1842
00:42:44.729 --> 00:42:46.521
{\pos(289.275)}Walking to dance class.

1843
00:42:46.606 --> 00:42:48.565
{\pos(289.275)}Ya? Okay. fine.

1844
00:42:48.649 --> 00:42:52.486
{\pos(289.275)}You just keep walking.
because I'm really not
driving you!

1845
00:42:52.570 --> 00:42:53.779
{\pos(289.275)}MARGO: Okay.

1846
00:42:53.863 --> 00:42:54.863
{\pos(289.275)}(SIGHS IN FRUSTRATION)

1847
00:42:55.281 --> 00:42:57.783
{\pos(289.275)}You're going to suffer
the wrath of Gru!

1848
00:42:58.242 --> 00:43:00.243
{\pos(289.275)}Seriously.
I'm going to
count to three!

1849
00:43:00.328 --> 00:43:02.287
{\pos(289.275)}And you had better
be in this car!

1850
00:43:02.371 --> 00:43:06.041
{\pos(289.275)}Here we go! One! Two!

1851
00:43:06.125 --> 00:43:09.711
{\pos(289.275)}INSTRUCTOR: Three.
four and five.

1852
00:43:09.796 --> 00:43:12.672
{\pos(289.275)}And lift. and stretch.

1853
00:43:12.757 --> 00:43:15.383
{\pos(289.275)}And one. and two...

1854
00:43:15.468 --> 00:43:17.594
{\pos(289.275)}Here you go.
What is it?

1855
00:43:17.678 --> 00:43:21.223
{\pos(289.275)}Your ticket
to the dance recital.
You are coming. right?

1856
00:43:21.307 --> 00:43:22.933
{\pos(289.275)}Of course.
of course.

1857
00:43:23.017 --> 00:43:26.102
{\pos(289.275)}I have pins and needles
that I'm sitting on.

1858
00:43:26.187 --> 00:43:27.854
{\pos(289.275)}Pinky promise?

1859
00:43:27.939 --> 00:43:29.231
{\pos(289.275)}(SIGHS)

1860
00:43:29.315 --> 00:43:32.526
{\pos(289.275)}Oh. yes.
My pinky promises.

1861
00:43:45.706 --> 00:43:50.377
{\pos(289.275)}All right.
Our first customer
is a man named Vector.

1862
00:43:50.461 --> 00:43:52.212
{\pos(289.275)}But he's a V.

1863
00:43:52.296 --> 00:43:54.297
{\pos(289.275)}You know. we're supposed
to start with the A's.

1864
00:43:54.382 --> 00:43:56.299
{\pos(289.275)}Then we go to the B's.
Then we...

1865
00:43:56.384 --> 00:43:58.802
{\pos(289.275)}Yes. yes!
I went to kindergarten.

1866
00:43:58.886 --> 00:44:01.304
{\pos(289.275)}I know how
the alphabet works!

1867
00:44:01.722 --> 00:44:03.098
{\pos(289.275)}(SIGHS)

1868
00:44:03.891 --> 00:44:06.560
{\pos(289.275)}I was just thinking

1869
00:44:06.644 --> 00:44:10.397
{\pos(289.275)}that it might be nice to
deliver Mr. Vector's first.

1870
00:44:10.481 --> 00:44:12.148
{\pos(289.275)}That is all.

1871
00:44:15.403 --> 00:44:17.904
{\pos(289.275)}Almost over.
It's almost over.

1872
00:44:20.032 --> 00:44:24.286
{\pos(289.275)}Girls.
welcome back to the fortress
of Vector-tude! (CHUCKLING)

1873
00:44:25.246 --> 00:44:27.747
{\pos(289.275)}Do you have
my cookies for me?

1874
00:44:35.506 --> 00:44:37.424
{\pos(289.275)}Four boxes of mini-mints.
two toffee totes.

1875
00:44:37.508 --> 00:44:42.220
{\pos(289.275)}two caramel clumpies
and fifteen boxes
of coco-nutties.

1876
00:44:42.305 --> 00:44:45.891
{\pos(289.275)}Exactly.
I'd like to see somebody else
order that many cookies.

1877
00:44:45.975 --> 00:44:47.017
{\pos(289.275)}Not likely.

1878
00:44:47.101 --> 00:44:49.185
{\pos(289.275)}Name one person
who ordered more
cookies than me.

1879
00:44:49.437 --> 00:44:50.979
{\pos(289.275)}That'll be $52.

1880
00:44:51.564 --> 00:44:52.856
{\pos(289.275)}Right.

1881
00:45:00.406 --> 00:45:03.116
{\pos(289.275)}Seven. eight. nine...

1882
00:45:04.035 --> 00:45:06.578
{\pos(289.275)}Tic Tacs! Where was I?

1883
00:45:06.662 --> 00:45:09.873
{\pos(289.275)}Seven. eight. nine...

1884
00:45:09.957 --> 00:45:11.750
{\pos(289.275)}Why are you
wearing pajamas?

1885
00:45:11.834 --> 00:45:16.129
{\pos(289.275)}(SCOFFING)
These aren't pajamas!
This is a warm-up suit.

1886
00:45:23.429 --> 00:45:24.971
{\pos(289.275)}(BLEEPING)

1887
00:45:32.813 --> 00:45:35.190
{\pos(289.275)}What are you
warming up for?
Stuff.

1888
00:45:35.274 --> 00:45:36.274
{\pos(289.275)}What sort of stuff?

1889
00:45:36.359 --> 00:45:38.777
{\pos(289.275)}Super-cool stuff
you wouldn't understand.

1890
00:45:38.861 --> 00:45:40.278
{\pos(289.275)}Like sleeping?

1891
00:45:40.363 --> 00:45:43.281
{\pos(289.275)}They are not pajamas!

1892
00:45:51.165 --> 00:45:52.832
{\pos(289.275)}(ALL GRUNTING)

1893
00:45:55.127 --> 00:45:58.338
{\pos(289.275)}Here you go. 52 big ones.

1894
00:46:07.640 --> 00:46:08.932
{\pos(289.275)}(GASPS)

1895
00:46:09.016 --> 00:46:10.684
{\pos(289.275)}(EXCLAIMS IN FRUSTRATION)

1896
